         <abstract>
            <p>This article provides a program that allows faculty members to write in seconds whole pages of printed comments about a student's discourses and essay examinations. The article discusses the computer program and accompanying bank of stored comments found useful in commenting on student writing in a college composition class. The same program could be used for any class including poetry, grammar, etc. This program utilizes the computer's abilities in such a way as to relieve the teacher of many administrative and time-consuming tasks.</p>
